&lt;Banco Santander> signed a letter ofintent with Bank of America &lt;BAC> to purchase its West Germanaffiliate &lt;Bankhaus Centrale Credit AG>, CC-Bank, the bank saidin a statement amplifying an earlier report from Frankfurt.    "The incorporation of CC-Bank in our group will provide amajor boost...For chanelling investment between Spain and theEuropean Community," the statement said.    "This operation enables us to take up a solid position inWest Germany ahead of Spain's full integration into the EC'sfinancial system in five years' time."    The deal included the license for Visa credit cards. REUTER&#3;